## ğŸ’» Project

This project is a clone of Twitter's user interface (UI) using React, focused on covering fundamental concepts of this technology such as **componentization, props, state, forms**, and more.

## ğŸš€ Technologies Used

This project was built with the following technologies:

- **HTML & CSS** - Structure and styling of the interface.
- **[React](https://reactjs.org/)** - JavaScript library for building dynamic user interfaces.
- **[Sass](https://sass-lang.com/)** - CSS preprocessor for better organization of styles.
- **[Vite](https://vitejs.dev/)** - Fast and efficient build tool for modern projects.

## ğŸ“‚ Project Structure

The directory structure is organized as follows:
```
- .github/
- public/
- src/
  - components/      # Reusable components
  - pages/           # Main application pages
  - styles/          # Global style files
  - main.tsx         # React entry point
  - App.tsx          # Main component
- index.html         # Main HTML file
- package.json       # Project dependencies
- vite.config.ts     # Vite configuration
```

